  "title": "IT Engineer (Manufacturing, SAP/EWM)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities: </strong></p><ul><li>Plan and implement international SAP EWM rollout projects.</li><li>Analyze requirements and design warehouse solutions with global and local stakeholders.</li><li>Manage and implement change requests.</li><li>Plan and oversee testing for new features.</li><li>Conduct user training and process standardisation workshops.</li><li>Provide first-level support and consultation to local users.</li><li>Collaborate within a global team with shared responsibility.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements: </strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Computer Science, or related field.</li><li>Strong knowledge of SAP EWM Customising and related modules (MM, PM, QM).</li><li>Good hands-on experience with ABAP/OO.</li><li>Experience with S/4HANA and SAP EWM RF Framework.</li></ul><p><strong>______________________________________________________</strong></p><p><strong>HOW TO APPLY :</strong></p><p><strong>Interested candidates, please submit your resume by clicking on “Quick Apply” or contact win@hkmsvs.com for more details.</strong></p><p><strong>Please provide following information in the resume for immediate processing</strong></p><p><strong>1) Reasons for leaving current and/or last employment</strong></p><p><strong>2) Last drawn and/or current salary</strong></p><p><strong>3) Expected salary</strong></p><p><strong>4) Date of availability and/or Notice Period</strong></p><p><strong>All applications will be treated in strictest confidence and only shortlisted candidates will be notified</strong></p><p><strong>Wee Wai Dan</strong></p><p><strong>EA License No : 03C5391</strong></p><p><strong>EA Reg No : R22109628</strong></p>",
